The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Knights interview coaches
                                                   Knights interview coaches
            OUR CORRESPONDENT                      
	Mumbai: The Kolkata Knight Riders (KKR) began their hunt for a coach with a string of interviews, including that of former Pakistan coach Richard Pybus, at franchise owner Shah Rukh Khans residence, here on Saturday.         
	South African Pybus was among the three who turned up for the for an interview for the post left vacant following the sacking of former Australian coach John Buchanan in the wake of a disastrous showing in the second edition of the IPL earlier this year.         
	Former India players Lalchand Rajput and Ashok Malhotra were the other two who met the KKR team management at the Bollywood stars bungalow Mannat Saturday evening.         
	They had called me to make a presentation. Its too early to say anything They have a few more people to interview Sunday as well, Rajput told The Telegraph.         
	Former Australian ODI stalwart Michael Bevan too is in the city and will also present his case while ex-England player Dermot Reeve was to arrive later in the night.         
	The KKR officials were tight-lipped about the series of interviews, which were to resume on Sunday when KKRs icon player Sourav Ganguly too is expected to join the team management.         
	Former India coach John Wright and former India international WV Raman are also among the contenders who are supposed to meet the KKR management in the coming days.                                                                                                                       
